HEADWORD: Shagbark
<hw>Shag"bark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
rough-barked species of hickory (<spn>Carya alba</spn>), its nut. Called
also <altname>shellbark</altname>. See <er>Hickory</er>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The West Indian <spn>Pithecolobium micradenium</spn>,
a legiminous tree with a red coiled-up pod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shagebush</ent>⟦br⟧
